	<div class="entry-author-malcolmgladwell entry-type-post entry" id="entry-6a00d83451c8bb69e20133f000ffed970b">
       <div class="entry-inner">
					<h3 class="entry-header"><a href="https://gladwell.typepad.com/gladwellcom/2010/06/my-greatest-triumph-.html">My greatest triumph! </a></h3>
		



		<div class="entry-content">

			<div class="entry-body">
				<p>Sorry. I can&#39;t resist. John Carson, a fellow runner from Canada, unearthed this photo from the archives of the Toronto Star. It&#39;s the finals of the 1500 meters at the Ontario 14-year-old championships, many many years ago. The runner on the left is Dave Reid, who was the greatest Canadian miler of his generation. I will only say this: in this particular race, Reid placed second. I &quot;retired&quot; from competitive running a year later, in large part because I realized that the particular statistical fluke represented by me beating Dave Reid was unlikely to ever be repeated. (For the runners out there, I believe I ran something like 4:05.)&#0160;</p><p> 
<a href="https://gladwell.typepad.com/.a/6a00d83451c8bb69e20133efe9cae3970b-pi" style="display: inline;"><img alt="Malcolm and dave" border="0" class="asset asset-image at-xid-6a00d83451c8bb69e20133efe9cae3970b image-full " src="https://gladwell.typepad.com/.a/6a00d83451c8bb69e20133efe9cae3970b-800wi" title="Malcolm and dave" /></a> <br />&#0160;</p><p></p>
			</div>
			


<!-- SIGNATURE -->




			
